description:
Microsoft cofounder Bill Gates discusses his new memoir and reflections from Microsoft's first 50 years. 

Chapters: 
0:00 - Introduction
2:01 - Early days working in tech
7:15 - Microsoft's beginnings: a computer on every desk and in every home
10:58 - Looking ahead at the future impact of tech
14:31 - Philanthropy and foundation work
18:53 - Reflections on leadership and legacy
20:51 - On maintaining a sense of humor
22:41 - Reflections on Satya Nadella as CEO
24:24 - Closing thoughts
